This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Country programmes are efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality programming standards in achieving results for children

title.narrative: C4D/SBC

description.narrative: C4D;supported COVID-19 prevention and promotion of COVID vaccination to inform public about key COVID-19 preventive measures and promote demand for COVID vaccination as well as maternal and child health care practices in the context of COVID. Accountability to affected populations (AAP) mainly focused on the involvement of beneficiaries in UNICEF programming by ensuring the voices from beneficiaries are captured through different channels. The feedback and inputs gathered from affected populations are analyzed and shared with relevant stakeholders for course correction and informed decision making. Technical support and capacity building was provided to partners, where there is an identified need. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:11/01/2022
